==French==
===Etymology===
Old French [[gaire]], from Frankish ''*waigaro'' ‘a lot’.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/gɛʀ/}}
:*'''Homophones:''' [[guerre]]

===Adverb===
'''guère'''
# [[hardly]], [[barely]]
#:''Pour me réchauffer, il n'y a guère qu'un pot de thé ''
#::''To warm myself up, there's hardly a pot of tea''
#:''Je ne vais guère mieux.''
#::''I'm not much better.''

===Usage notes===
*''Guère'' is used with ''[[ne#French|ne]]'' as a negative construction; its etymological meaning is ‘not....very much’.

